Detailed Description

And now we have our container.

The buffer for the current ogMap image and the time at which it occured. The images and corresponding times are put into seperate ques, the ques are filled by the imageCallback()/thread in realtime. The images are generated from robot sensor data. The mutex lock is reqired to access the ques as they are shared by a number of theads. This thread is spawned by the ROS main thread. The sepreateThread() thread is used to process this data.
